de.ovgu.featureide.fm.core.functional

Interface Functional.IBinaryFunction<T,U,R>

  • Enclosing class:
    Functional

    public static interface Functional.IBinaryFunction<T,U,R>
    Represents a function that takes two arguments of type T and U. It returns a result of type R.

    Example The following example shows a function which takes two integer and converts the sum of these to its string representation (Java 1.8 syntax used). IBinaryFunction<Integer, Integer, String> toString = (a,b) ⇒ { new Integer(a.intValue() + b.intValue()).toString() }; String seven = toString(2,5); // seven.equals("7")
    Since:
    3.0
    Author:
    Marcus Pinnecke
